President Biden has declared a major disaster in Missouri due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred on December 10, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. DuWayne Tewes has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.